About Us

In 2005, while working for the original McGill family business The North Rocks Greenery, Jon took on his first Garden Maintenance job armed with just a pair of secateurs.

While under that name they grew significantly and expanded to Landscaping. The McGill family then re-branded that side of the business after selling the Nursery.

Under it's new name, Looking Up Landscapes, the business has moved away from Garden Maintenance to focus on Landscaping services and shifted their area of work to encompass the Central Coast, Lake Macquarie area, the Hunter Valley and Newcastle.

Our Values

Integrity: We seek to provide a quality product, informed by your desires and expectations, for a price that genuinely represents that product.

Excellence: We seek to go beyond ‘good enough’ to ‘really well done’. Providing a product that lasts, that achieves results aesthetically and functionally and, ultimately, exceeds your expectations.

Genuine Care: We seek to be people who provide not just a physical product, but a valuable service that is sensitive to needs of each customer as well as their personal and family space.
